Mapfluence Session Notes
Date: 2026-03-18

User workflow preferences
- Commit and push to `main` after completed code changes until the user says otherwise.
- Keep practical, restart-safe notes in this `.mb` file.

Current Hastings map architecture target
- Admin full map: `/:universityId/admin` (Mapfluence edit + AI + planning tools).
- Admin combined stakeholder + technical: `/:universityId/admin/engagement`.
- Public stakeholder engagement: `/:universityId/engagement`.
- Public technical assessment: `/:universityId/technical`.

Latest completed work
- Removed `/:universityId/admin/technical` route.
- Kept technical routes in public shell and restored technical assessment loading there.
- Allowed marker placement in admin engagement map (assessment view), while preventing placement during technical panel view.
- Hid full Mapfluence/space-export/planning/AI blocks from technical-only mode.
- Enabled admin sign-in controls on technical pages for authorized saves.

Latest completed work (follow-up hardening)
- Added explicit route-mode header text in controls so each URL clearly labels its purpose.
- Kept controls toggle available on technical routes (not just admin) for cleaner presentation.
- Added map-view/panel sync: technical panel now auto-opens when entering Technical view with a selected building and closes when leaving Technical view.
- Added route guard cleanup so non-full-admin routes auto-close Mapfluence-only AI/room-edit overlays.
- Added route guard cleanup so planning scenario mode is forced off outside the full admin map.

Latest completed work (technical autosave)
- Added debounced local draft autosave for Technical Assessment edits.
- Drafts are keyed by university + building and restore automatically when reopening that building.
- Added in-panel save state messaging: Unsaved, Saving draft, Draft restored/saved, Saving to cloud, Saved to cloud, and Error.
- Kept cloud save as explicit admin-only action and added non-admin hint that local drafts are still being preserved.

Latest completed work (admin combined workflow)
- Added `Workflow Focus` quick chips in `/admin/engagement`:
  - Stakeholder Focus
  - Technical Focus
- Stakeholder Focus sets assessment view and emphasizes marker/heatmap workflow.
- Technical Focus jumps to technical view and quiets engagement heat/sentiment overlays for cleaner assessment work.

Latest completed work (workflow separation refinement)
- In `/admin/engagement`, workflow options are now `Stakeholder` and `Technical` (renamed from `Assessment`).
- Stakeholder workflow now shows only stakeholder tools (markers/heatmap/sentiment controls).
- Technical workflow now hides stakeholder tools and surfaces only technical assessment behavior.
- Added a stakeholder building-condition toggle in combined mode to enable/disable whole-building stakeholder condition editing panel.
- Prevented stakeholder marker popup from opening on building clicks when building-condition editing is enabled.
- In `/technical`, workflow dropdown now contains only `Technical` (no `Assessment` option).
